{"type":"message","id":"dcf3295a","parentId":"3bb591f0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:11:53.950Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8qtrimhi8ej1_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 081114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked as complete\r\n2. There's been significant synthesis work done - architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, compression-causal duality\r\n3. The key pending action is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. The success criteria are: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n5. This needs to be tested on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe next logical action is to implement the TIC classifier. This is a concrete step that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse log files\r\n2. Implements the TIC classifier (temporal invariance compression)\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis would be a new file in the sandbox.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next concrete step for Phase 1 advancement. The pulse logs exist but no TIC classifier is yet implemented to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment to classify pulse content as invariant/variant and predict next-pulse content from past invariants.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d+)\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse log files, sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            date, seq = match.groups()\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\r\n                \"file\": f.name,\r\n                \"date\": date,\r\n                \"seq\": int(seq),\r\n                \"content\": content\r\n            })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract simple features for classification.\"\"\"\r\n    words = content.split()\r\n    lines = content.strip().split('\\n')\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"word_count\": len(words),\r\n        \"line_count\": len(lines),\r\n        \"has_mutation\": \"### MUTATION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_action\": \"### ACTION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_observation\": \"### OBSERVATION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_goal_ref\": \"goal\" in content.lower(),\r\n        \"has_file_ref\": bool(re.search(r\"\\b\\w+\\.\\w+\\b\", content)),  # filenames\r\n        \"has_code_block\": \"```\" in content,\r\n        \"first_word\": words[0] if words else \"\",\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Find invariant features that persist across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if not pulses:\r\n        return {}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract features for all pulses\r\n    all_features = [extract_features(p[\"content\"]) for p in pulses]\r\n    \r\n    # Find features with low variance (invariants)\r\n    invariants = {}\r\n    for key in all_features[0].keys():\r\n        if key == \"first_word\":\r\n            continue  # Skip categorical for now\r\n        values = [f[key] for f in all_features]\r\n        # For boolean features, check consistency\r\n        if all(isinstance(v, bool) for v in values):\r\n            true_count = sum(1 for v in values if v)\r\n            invariants[key] = {\r\n                \"true_ratio\": true_count / len(values),\r\n                \"is_invariant\": true_count > len(values) * 0.8 or true_count < len(values) * 0.2\r\n            }\r\n        else:\r\n            # For numeric, compute variance\r\n            mean = sum(values) / len(values)\r\n            variance = sum((v - mean) ** 2 for v in values) / len(values)\r\n            invariants[key] = {\r\n                \"mean\": mean,\r\n                \"variance\": variance,\r\n                \"is_invariant\": variance < mean * 0.1 if mean > 0 else True\r\n            }\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse(pulse, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a pulse as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    features = extract_features(pulse[\"content\"])\r\n    invariant_keys = [k for k, v in invariants.items() if v.get(\"is_invariant\", False)]\r\n    \r\n    invariant_score = sum(1 for k in invariant_keys if k in features and features[k])\r\n    total_invariants = len(invariant_keys)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"invariant_score\": invariant_score,\r\n        \"total_invariants\": total_invariants,\r\n        \"classification\": \"invariant_dominant\" if invariant_score > total_invariants * 0.5 else \"variant_dominant\",\r\n        \"ratio\": invariant_score / total_invariants if total_invariants > 0 else 0\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_pulse, past_pulses, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict characteristics of next pulse based on past invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(past_pulses) < 2:\r\n        return {\"prediction\": \"insufficient_data\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Find most recent invariant-dominant pulses\r\n    classifications = [classify_pulse(p, invariants) for p in past_pulses]\r\n    invariant_pulses = [p for p, c in\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:11:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354313948}}
